race.comment: BOTANICAL BOY (12) presented fitter again and landed the prize by 2.5 lengths here over 1430m as the public elect. Must raise the bar but he has weight relief and the talent to test this line-up. SUPERNIMA (6) is the threat building on his Pakenham win and a close-up effort at Caulfield Heath in stronger than this. Maps for the run of the race and the 3kg claim sees him very well placed. FIGLIO D'ARGENTO (14) quickly found his best leading and winning a 66 at Cranbourne. He will strip fitter and only has to hold that form to be right in the finish. MAGARTEN (9) resumed this grade at Mornington and appeared a run short. May need longer now, but he won't be far away. PUGLIA (16) has ability but will need a good ride from a tricky barrier.
